<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7865&amp;p=79919#p79919"><![CDATA[
Do you mean you are interested in the PSX or the Genesis? For Playstation dev you can look here: <a href="http://jum.pdroms.de/PSX/psxdevstart.html" class="postlink">http://jum.pdroms.de/PSX/psxdevstart.html</a>. It's very similar to the PSP in terms of hardware and kernel structure (which is <a href="http://www.psp-programming.com/tutorials/c/lesson01.htm" class="postlink">very well documented</a>), although the APIs and hardware are a lot different. There's also a lot less RAM and a much slower clock speed.<br /><br />Also there is a lot more assembly done on the PSX due to the lower clock speed, and the low-level graphics interface is much different.<br /><br />So yea, I guess it's <em>kinda</em> like the PSP <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3706">qbradq</a> — Thu Jun 16, 2011 12:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
