<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7865&amp;p=79902#p79902"><![CDATA[
For me there are two reasons why I did not get into Genesis development.<br /><br />1. The graphics on the Genesis are a bit beyond my reach as far as creating them.<br />2. I have very little nostalgia for that system, and that's a big motivator for me.<br /><br />These points are also the reasons I have not pursued development on the PSP (other than some kernel-mode stuff), PSX, GBA, DS and Jaguar. Point 1 also applies to the SNES, and point 2 applies to everything released before the NES.<br /><br />I guess I'm kinda like a dog that's finally found a place to sleep <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3706">qbradq</a> — Thu Jun 16, 2011 6:38 am</p><hr />
