<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7865&amp;p=79892#p79892"><![CDATA[
There is a rumor that Mega Man The Wily Wars was programmed in C for Genesis and is the explanation for why the game suffers from A LOT of slowdown compared to the NES versions. Seriously the game slows down while fighting CutMan if he throws his projectile as I recall which the NES version didn't. <br /><br />That's not to say that you couldn't make a decent game in C for Genesis. Maybe 68000 compilers generate better code today too. But as with any system certain things will discourage homebrew development such as Sound &amp; Music tools as well as alternative development platforms that may be more appealing or easier.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Wed Jun 15, 2011 8:35 pm</p><hr />
